{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":823,"text":"So I come from the tallest\npeople on the planet --"},{"time":3215,"text":"the Dutch."},{"time":5383,"text":"It hasn't always been this way."},{"time":7093,"text":"In fact, all across the globe,\npeople have been gaining height."},{"time":10331,"text":"In the last 150 years,"},{"time":11918,"text":"in developed countries,"},{"time":13103,"text":"on average, we have gotten\n10 centimeters taller."},{"time":16139,"text":"And scientists have a lot\nof theories about why this is,"},{"time":18942,"text":"but almost all of them involve nutrition,"},{"time":21386,"text":"namely the increase of dairy and meat."}]},{"cues":[{"time":24432,"text":"In the last 50 years,"},{"time":25964,"text":"global meat consumption\nhas more than quadrupled,"},{"time":28862,"text":"from 71 million tons to 310 million tons."},{"time":32705,"text":"Something similar has been going on\nwith milk and eggs."},{"time":36460,"text":"In every society where incomes have risen,\nso has protein consumption."},{"time":41053,"text":"And we know that globally,\nwe are getting richer."},{"time":44006,"text":"And as the middle class is on the rise,\nso is our global population,"},{"time":47235,"text":"from 7 billion of us today\nto 9.7 billion by 2050,"},{"time":52210,"text":"which means that by 2050,"},{"time":53697,"text":"we are going to need at least\n70 percent more protein"},{"time":56248,"text":"than what is available to humankind today."},{"time":59322,"text":"And the latest prediction of the UN\nputs that population number,"},{"time":62365,"text":"by the end of this century, at 11 billion,"},{"time":64849,"text":"which means that we are going\nto need a lot more protein."}]},{"cues":[{"time":69027,"text":"This challenge is staggering --"},{"time":70590,"text":"so much so, that recently,"},{"time":72421,"text":"a team at Anglia Ruskin\nGlobal Sustainability Institute suggested"},{"time":75563,"text":"that if we don't change\nour global policies"},{"time":77723,"text":"and food production systems,"},{"time":79295,"text":"our societies might actually collapse\nin the next 30 years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":84143,"text":"Currently, our ocean serves\nas the main source of animal protein."},{"time":88487,"text":"Over 2.6 billion people\ndepend on it every single day."},{"time":93177,"text":"At the same time,"},{"time":94384,"text":"our global fisheries\nare two-and-a-half times larger"},{"time":97059,"text":"than what our oceans\ncan sustainably support,"},{"time":99607,"text":"meaning that humans take\nfar more fish from the ocean"},{"time":102353,"text":"than the oceans can naturally replace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":104681,"text":"WWF recently published a report\nshowing that just in the last 40 years,"},{"time":109497,"text":"our global marine life\nhas been slashed in half."},{"time":112595,"text":"And another recent report suggests\nthat of our largest predatory species,"},{"time":117322,"text":"such as swordfish and bluefin tuna,"},{"time":119694,"text":"over 90 percent has disappeared\nsince the 1950s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123653,"text":"And there are a lot of great, sustainable\nfishing initiatives across the planet"},{"time":127450,"text":"working towards better practices\nand better-managed fisheries."},{"time":131080,"text":"But ultimately,"},{"time":132255,"text":"all of these initiatives are working\ntowards keeping current catch constant."},{"time":136564,"text":"It's unlikely,"},{"time":137739,"text":"even with the best-managed fisheries,"},{"time":139553,"text":"that we are going to be able to take\nmuch more from the ocean"},{"time":142540,"text":"than we do today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":143719,"text":"We have to stop plundering\nour oceans the way we have."},{"time":146488,"text":"We need to alleviate the pressure on it."},{"time":148670,"text":"And we are at a point"},{"time":150012,"text":"where if we push much harder\nfor more produce,"},{"time":152801,"text":"we might face total collapse."},{"time":155226,"text":"Our current systems are not going to feed\na growing global population."}]},{"cues":[{"time":160860,"text":"So how do we fix this?"},{"time":162153,"text":"What's the world going to look like\nin just 35 short years"},{"time":164915,"text":"when there's 2.7 billion more of us\nsharing the same resources?"},{"time":169059,"text":"We could all become vegan."},{"time":170955,"text":"Sounds like a great idea,"},{"time":172732,"text":"but it's not realistic"},{"time":174060,"text":"and it's impossibly hard\nto mandate globally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176977,"text":"People are eating animal protein\nwhether we like it or not."},{"time":180564,"text":"And suppose we fail to change our ways"},{"time":182420,"text":"and continue on the current path,"},{"time":184570,"text":"failing to meet demands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186428,"text":"The World Health Organization\nrecently reported"},{"time":188674,"text":"that 800 million people are suffering\nfrom malnutrition and food shortage,"},{"time":192860,"text":"which is due to that same\ngrowing, global population"},{"time":196295,"text":"and the declining access to resources\nlike water, energy and land."},{"time":201212,"text":"It takes very little imagination"},{"time":203296,"text":"to picture a world of global unrest,\nriots and further malnutrition."},{"time":208270,"text":"People are hungry,"},{"time":209920,"text":"and we are running dangerously low\non natural resources."},{"time":213328,"text":"For so, so many reasons,"},{"time":214908,"text":"we need to change our global\nfood production systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":218255,"text":"We must do better"},{"time":219703,"text":"and there is a solution."},{"time":220892,"text":"And that solution lies in aquaculture --"},{"time":223501,"text":"the farming of fish, plants like seaweed,\nshellfish and crustaceans."},{"time":227861,"text":"As the great ocean hero\nJacques Cousteau once said,"},{"time":230314,"text":"\"We must start using the ocean\nas farmers instead of hunters."},{"time":233212,"text":"That's what civilization is all about --\nfarming instead of hunting.\""},{"time":237402,"text":"Fish is the last food that we hunt."}]},{"cues":[{"time":240374,"text":"And why is it that we keep\nhearing phrases like,"},{"time":243706,"text":"\"Life's too short for farmed fish,\""},{"time":245413,"text":"or, \"Wild-caught, of course!\""},{"time":247025,"text":"over fish that we know\nvirtually nothing about?"},{"time":249398,"text":"We don't know what it ate\nduring its lifetime,"},{"time":251633,"text":"and we don't know what\npollution it encounters."},{"time":253829,"text":"And if it was a large predatory species,"},{"time":255773,"text":"it might have gone through the coast\nof Fukushima yesterday."},{"time":258626,"text":"We don't know."},{"time":259994,"text":"Very few people realize"},{"time":261361,"text":"the traceability in fisheries\nnever goes beyond the hunter"},{"time":265027,"text":"that caught the wild animal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266566,"text":"But let's back up for a second"},{"time":268027,"text":"and talk about why fish\nis the best food choice."},{"time":270638,"text":"It's healthy,"},{"time":271813,"text":"it prevents heart disease,"},{"time":273093,"text":"it provides key amino acids"},{"time":274560,"text":"and key fatty acids like Omega-3s,"},{"time":277337,"text":"which is very different from almost\nany other type of meat."},{"time":280238,"text":"And aside from being healthy,"},{"time":281872,"text":"it's also a lot more exciting and diverse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284493,"text":"Think about it -- most animal farming\nis pretty monotonous."},{"time":287700,"text":"Cow is cow, sheep is sheep, pig's pig,"},{"time":290375,"text":"and poultry -- turkey, duck, chicken --\npretty much sums it up."},{"time":294476,"text":"And then there's 500 species of fish\nbeing farmed currently."},{"time":299315,"text":"not that Western supermarkets\nreflect that on their shelves,"},{"time":302267,"text":"but that's beside that point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":303688,"text":"And you can farm fish\nin a very healthy manner"},{"time":306479,"text":"that's good for us, good for the planet\nand good for the fish."},{"time":310062,"text":"I know I sound fish-obsessed --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312022,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":314172,"text":"Let me explain:"},{"time":315347,"text":"My brilliant partner and wife,\nAmy Novograntz, and I got involved"},{"time":318530,"text":"in aquaculture a couple of years ago."},{"time":320505,"text":"We were inspired by Sylvia Earle,"},{"time":322801,"text":"who won the TED Prize in 2009."},{"time":325121,"text":"We actually met on Mission Blue I\nin the Galapagos."},{"time":329157,"text":"Amy was there as the TED Prize Director;"},{"time":331118,"text":"me, an entrepreneur from the Netherlands\nand concerned citizen,"},{"time":334332,"text":"love to dive, passion for the oceans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337292,"text":"Mission Blue truly changed our lives."},{"time":339650,"text":"We fell in love,"},{"time":340825,"text":"got married"},{"time":342325,"text":"and we came away really inspired,"},{"time":344590,"text":"thinking we really want to do something\nabout ocean conservation --"},{"time":347823,"text":"something that was meant to last,"},{"time":349582,"text":"that could make a real difference"},{"time":352162,"text":"and something that we could do together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":355741,"text":"Little did we expect that that would\nlead us to fish farming."},{"time":359741,"text":"But a few months after\nwe got off the boat,"},{"time":361863,"text":"we got to a meeting\nat Conservation International,"},{"time":364421,"text":"where the Director General of WorldFish\nwas talking about aquaculture,"},{"time":368472,"text":"asking a room full of environmentalists\nto stop turning from it,"},{"time":372242,"text":"realize what was going on"},{"time":374027,"text":"and to really get involved"},{"time":375472,"text":"because aquaculture has the potential"},{"time":377608,"text":"to be just what our oceans\nand populations need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381184,"text":"We were stunned when we heard the stats"},{"time":383091,"text":"that we didn't know more\nabout this industry already"},{"time":385651,"text":"and excited about the chance\nto help get it right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389042,"text":"And to talk about stats --"},{"time":390813,"text":"right now, the amount of fish\nconsumed globally,"},{"time":393613,"text":"wild catch and farmed combined,"},{"time":395693,"text":"is twice the tonnage\nof the total amount of beef"},{"time":398049,"text":"produced on planet earth last year."},{"time":400439,"text":"Every single fishing vessel combined,"},{"time":402770,"text":"small and large, across the globe,"},{"time":404725,"text":"together produce about 65 million tons\nof wild-caught seafood"},{"time":408626,"text":"for human consumption."}]},{"cues":[{"time":410623,"text":"Aquaculture this year,"},{"time":411953,"text":"for the first time in history,"},{"time":413556,"text":"actually produces more\nthan what we catch from the wild."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416874,"text":"But now this:"},{"time":418049,"text":"Demand is going to go up."},{"time":420157,"text":"In the next 35 years,"},{"time":421690,"text":"we are going to need an additional\n85 million tons to meet demand,"},{"time":426709,"text":"which is one-and-a-half times\nas much, almost,"},{"time":429328,"text":"as what we catch globally\nout of our oceans."},{"time":433140,"text":"An enormous number."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434812,"text":"It's safe to assume that that's not\ngoing to come from the ocean."},{"time":437935,"text":"It needs to come from farming."},{"time":440163,"text":"And talk about farming --"},{"time":441502,"text":"for farming you need resources."},{"time":444313,"text":"As a human needs to eat\nto grow and stay alive,"},{"time":447266,"text":"so does an animal."},{"time":448763,"text":"A cow needs to eat\neight to nine pounds of feed"},{"time":451682,"text":"and drink almost 8,000 liters of water"},{"time":454157,"text":"to create just one pound of meat."},{"time":456535,"text":"Experts agree that it's impossible"},{"time":458602,"text":"to farm cows for every\ninhabitant on this planet."},{"time":461778,"text":"We just don't have enough feed or water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464540,"text":"And we can't keep cutting down\nrain forests for it."},{"time":467318,"text":"And fresh water -- planet earth\nhas a very limited supply."},{"time":470851,"text":"We need something more efficient"},{"time":472986,"text":"to keep humankind alive on this planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476517,"text":"And now let's compare\nthat with fish farming."},{"time":479164,"text":"You can farm one pound of fish\nwith just one pound of feed,"},{"time":483126,"text":"and depending on species, even less."},{"time":485845,"text":"And why is that?"},{"time":488099,"text":"Well, that's because fish,\nfirst of all, float."},{"time":490892,"text":"They don't need to stand around all day\nresisting gravity like we do."},{"time":494806,"text":"And most fish are cold-blooded --"},{"time":496584,"text":"they don't need to heat themselves."},{"time":498288,"text":"Fish chills."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499480,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":501125,"text":"And it needs very little water,"},{"time":502689,"text":"which is counterintuitive,"},{"time":503991,"text":"but as we say,"},{"time":505402,"text":"it swims in it but it hardly drinks it."},{"time":507820,"text":"Fish are the most resource-efficient\nanimal protein available to humankind,"},{"time":512257,"text":"aside from insects."}]},{"cues":[{"time":515297,"text":"How much we've learned since."},{"time":517482,"text":"For example, on top of that\n65 million tons that's annually caught"},{"time":520943,"text":"for human consumption,"},{"time":522577,"text":"there's an additional 30 million tons\ncaught for animal feed,"},{"time":526588,"text":"mostly sardines and anchovies\nfor the aquaculture industry"},{"time":530153,"text":"that's turned into fish meal and fish oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532602,"text":"This is madness."},{"time":534548,"text":"Sixty-five percent of these fisheries,\nglobally, are badly managed."},{"time":538144,"text":"Some of the worst issues\nof our time are connected to it."},{"time":540878,"text":"It's destroying our oceans."},{"time":542200,"text":"The worst slavery issues\nimaginable are connected to it."},{"time":545702,"text":"Recently, an article came out of Stanford"},{"time":548536,"text":"saying that if 50 percent\nof the world's aquaculture industry"},{"time":551433,"text":"would stop using fish meal,"},{"time":552759,"text":"our oceans would be saved."},{"time":554837,"text":"Now think about that for a minute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556516,"text":"Now, we know that the oceans\nhave far more problems --"},{"time":559560,"text":"they have pollution,\nthere's acidification,"},{"time":562369,"text":"coral reef destruction and so on."},{"time":563976,"text":"But it underlines the impact\nof our fisheries,"},{"time":566537,"text":"and it underlines how\ninterconnected everything is."},{"time":569608,"text":"Fisheries, aquaculture, deforestation,"},{"time":573248,"text":"climate change, food security and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576834,"text":"In the search for alternatives,"},{"time":578360,"text":"the industry, on a massive scale,"},{"time":580439,"text":"has reverted to plant-based alternatives"},{"time":582626,"text":"like soy, industrial chicken waste,"},{"time":585503,"text":"blood meal from slaughterhouses"},{"time":587369,"text":"and so on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588648,"text":"And we understand where\nthese choices come from,"},{"time":591136,"text":"but this is not the right approach."},{"time":593289,"text":"It's not sustainable,"},{"time":594568,"text":"it's not healthy."},{"time":595766,"text":"Have you ever seen a chicken\nat the bottom of the ocean?"},{"time":598453,"text":"Of course not."},{"time":599828,"text":"If you feed salmon soy with nothing else,"},{"time":602048,"text":"it literally explodes."},{"time":604463,"text":"Salmon is a carnivore,"},{"time":605639,"text":"it has no way to digest soy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":609049,"text":"Now, fish farming is by far"},{"time":611195,"text":"the best animal farming\navailable to humankind."},{"time":613536,"text":"But it's had a really bad reputation."},{"time":616373,"text":"There's been excessive use of chemicals,"},{"time":618576,"text":"there's been virus and disease\ntransfered to wild populations,"},{"time":621780,"text":"ecosystem destruction and pollution,"},{"time":624133,"text":"escaped fish breeding\nwith wild populations,"},{"time":626371,"text":"altering the overall genetic pool,"},{"time":628395,"text":"and then of course, as just mentioned,"},{"time":630885,"text":"the unsustainable feed ingredients."}]},{"cues":[{"time":633396,"text":"How blessed were the days"},{"time":634663,"text":"when we could just enjoy\nfood that was on our plate,"},{"time":637134,"text":"whatever it was."},{"time":638825,"text":"Once you know, you know."},{"time":640388,"text":"You can't go back."},{"time":641618,"text":"It's not fun."},{"time":642793,"text":"We really need a transparent food\nsystem that we can trust,"},{"time":646006,"text":"that produces healthy food."}]},{"cues":[{"time":648726,"text":"But the good news is"},{"time":649949,"text":"that decades of development and research"},{"time":652886,"text":"have led to a lot of new\ntechnologies and knowledge"},{"time":655372,"text":"that allow us to do a lot better."},{"time":657208,"text":"We can now farm fish\nwithout any of these issues."}]},{"cues":[{"time":660548,"text":"I think of agriculture\nbefore the green revolution --"},{"time":663453,"text":"we are at aquaculture\nand the blue revolution."},{"time":667817,"text":"New technologies means"},{"time":669078,"text":"that we can now produce a feed\nthat's perfectly natural,"},{"time":672670,"text":"with a minimal footprint"},{"time":673878,"text":"that consists of microbes, insects,\nseaweeds and micro-algae."},{"time":678689,"text":"Healthy for the people,"},{"time":680016,"text":"healthy for the fish,"},{"time":681191,"text":"healthy for the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683293,"text":"Microbes, for example,"},{"time":684467,"text":"can be a perfect alternative\nfor high-grade fish meal --"},{"time":687340,"text":"at scale."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688801,"text":"Insects are the --"},{"time":690908,"text":"well, first of all, the perfect recycling"},{"time":692893,"text":"because they're grown on food waste;"},{"time":694647,"text":"but second,"},{"time":695823,"text":"think of fly-fishing,"},{"time":696998,"text":"and you know how logical\nit actually is to use it as fish feed."},{"time":700712,"text":"You don't need large tracts of land for it"},{"time":702759,"text":"and you don't need\nto cut down rain forests for it."},{"time":705870,"text":"And microbes and insects are actually\nnet water producers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":709509,"text":"This revolution is starting as we speak,"},{"time":711762,"text":"it just needs scale."},{"time":714492,"text":"We can now farm far more\nspecies than ever before"},{"time":717583,"text":"in controlled, natural conditions,\ncreating happy fish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":721897,"text":"I imagine, for example,"},{"time":723205,"text":"a closed system that's performing\nmore efficiently than insect farming,"},{"time":728837,"text":"where you can produce\nhealthy, happy, delicious fish"},{"time":732105,"text":"with little or no effluent,"},{"time":733501,"text":"almost no energy and almost no water"},{"time":735985,"text":"and a natural feed\nwith a minimal footprint."},{"time":739084,"text":"Or a system where you grow\nup to 10 species next to each other --"},{"time":742335,"text":"off of each other,"},{"time":743735,"text":"mimicking nature."},{"time":745918,"text":"You need very little feed,"},{"time":747312,"text":"very little footprint."},{"time":748558,"text":"I think of seaweed growing\noff the effluent of fish, for example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754453,"text":"There's great technologies\npopping up all over the globe."},{"time":757574,"text":"From alternatives to battle disease"},{"time":759777,"text":"so we don't need antibiotics\nand chemicals anymore,"},{"time":762666,"text":"to automated feeders that feel\nwhen the fish are hungry,"},{"time":766346,"text":"so we can save on feed\nand create less pollution."},{"time":770016,"text":"Software systems that gather\ndata across farms,"},{"time":772643,"text":"so we can improve farm practices."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775127,"text":"There's really cool stuff\nhappening all over the globe."},{"time":778670,"text":"And make no mistake --\nall of these things are possible"},{"time":781337,"text":"at a cost that's competitive\nto what a farmer spends today."},{"time":785024,"text":"Tomorrow, there will be no excuse\nfor anyone to not do the right thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790164,"text":"So somebody needs to connect the dots"},{"time":792447,"text":"and give these developments\na big kick in the butt."},{"time":795054,"text":"And that's what we've been working on\nthe last couple of years,"},{"time":798095,"text":"and that's what we need\nto be working on together --"},{"time":801049,"text":"rethinking everything from the ground up,"},{"time":803424,"text":"with a holistic view\nacross the value chain,"},{"time":805967,"text":"connecting all these things\nacross the globe,"},{"time":808125,"text":"alongside great entrepreneurs"},{"time":810197,"text":"that are willing to share\na collective vision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813474,"text":"Now is the time to create\nchange in this industry"},{"time":816331,"text":"and to push it into\na sustainable direction."},{"time":818566,"text":"This industry is still young,"},{"time":820012,"text":"much of its growth is still ahead."},{"time":822041,"text":"It's a big task, but not\nas far-fetched as you might think."},{"time":824899,"text":"It's possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":827032,"text":"So we need to take pressure off the ocean."},{"time":829233,"text":"We want to eat good and healthy."},{"time":830804,"text":"And if we eat an animal,\nit needs to be one"},{"time":832900,"text":"that had a happy and healthy life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":834582,"text":"We need to have a meal that we can trust,"},{"time":836813,"text":"live long lives."},{"time":838577,"text":"And this is not just for people\nin San Francisco or Northern Europe --"},{"time":842500,"text":"this is for all of us."},{"time":844370,"text":"Even in the poorest countries,"},{"time":846054,"text":"it's not just about money."},{"time":847588,"text":"People prefer something fresh\nand healthy that they can trust"},{"time":851428,"text":"over something that comes from far away\nthat they know nothing about."},{"time":855244,"text":"We're all the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858267,"text":"The day will come"},{"time":859442,"text":"where people will realize -- no, demand --\nfarmed fish on their plate"},{"time":862727,"text":"that's farmed well\nand that's farmed healthy --"},{"time":866204,"text":"and refuse anything less."}]},{"cues":[{"time":867482,"text":"You can help speed this up."},{"time":869163,"text":"Ask questions when you order seafood."},{"time":871545,"text":"Where does my fish come from?"},{"time":873426,"text":"Who raised it,"},{"time":874965,"text":"and what did it eat?"},{"time":877008,"text":"Information about where your fish\ncomes from and how it was produced"},{"time":880691,"text":"needs to be much more readily available."},{"time":883663,"text":"And consumers need to put pressure\non the aquaculture industry"},{"time":886871,"text":"to do the right thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":888653,"text":"So every time you order,"},{"time":890720,"text":"ask for detail"},{"time":892711,"text":"and show that you really care\nabout what you eat"},{"time":895217,"text":"and what's been given to you."},{"time":896999,"text":"And eventually, they will listen."},{"time":899367,"text":"And all of us will benefit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901575,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":902750,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}